Credit-Default Swaps on Portugal Jump to 552, Approach 555 Jan. 10 Record

-- B y   A b i g a i l   M o s e s
-- 
2011-03-24T08:34:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/credit-default-swaps-on-portugal-jump-to-552-approach-555-jan-10-record.html
The cost of insuring Portuguese
government debt jumped 17.5 basis points to 552, approaching the
record 555 basis points Jan. 10, according to CMA prices for
credit-default swaps.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Abigail Moses in London at 
 amoses5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
